    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the species Acer negundo, native to the northeastern North America east of the Rocky Mountains. It is used for crates, furniture, paper pulp, and charcoal. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
